NDReg LDDMM (Non-Linear)¶

This is a non-linear registration algorithm. It finds the "best" way to register an input image to a reference image by minimizing a cost function. The goal is to minimize the energy function of both images.

Specifically, the algorithm uses a generic MI matching term, thus finding the optimal control which aligns the input to the target. The optimization step iterates through the possible I until the optimal control is found. The velocity iterations are calculated using gradient descent.

We will qualitatively assess the simulations by overlaying the reference and registered images. We will quantitatively assess the simulations by plotting the MSE of each registration.

We will qualitatively assess the real data by overlaying the reference and registered images. We will quantitatively assess the real data by plotting the MSE of each registration, and by calculating the discriminability of the extracted ROI timeseries.

from ndreg import *
import math
import numpy as np
import SimpleITK as itk
import nibabel as nb

preGoodSimNdregErrors = []
postGoodSimNdregErrors = []

for iters in range(10):
    print("sim " + str(iters))
    
    n = 100
    a = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    b = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    c = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    d = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    e = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    f = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    r = np.random.randint(low=n*0.1, high=n*0.25, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    y,x = np.ogrid[-a:n-a, -b:n-b]
    v,w = np.ogrid[-d:n-d, -e:n-e]
    mask = x*x + y*y <= r*r
    mask2 = w*w + v*v <= r*r

    checkers = 255*np.ones((n,n))
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            if (i % (n/5) == 0) and (j % (n/5) == 0):
                checkers[i:i+(n/10), j:j+(n/10)] = 128
            if (i % (n/5) == (n/10)) and (j % (n/5) == (n/10)):
                checkers[i:i+(n/10), j:j+(n/10)] = 128
        
    inData = np.zeros((n,n))
    inData[(d-r):(d+r),(e-r):(e+r)] = checkers[(d-r):(d+r),(e-r):(e+r)]
    #inData = inData.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    inImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(inData)
    refData = np.zeros((n,n))
    refData[mask2] = checkers[mask2]
    #refData = refData.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(refData)
    
    #inImg2 = imgRead("I0.tif")
    #refImg2 = imgRead("I1.tif")
    #inData2 = itk.GetArrayFromImage(inImg2)
    #refData2 = itk.GetArrayFromImage(refImg2)
    #refData2 = refData2.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    #inData2 = inData2.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    #inImg2 = itk.GetImageFromArray(inData2)
    #refImg2 = itk.GetImageFromArray(refData2)
    #plt.imshow(itk.GetArrayFromImage(refImg2 - refImg))
    #plt.imshow(itk.GetArrayFromImage(inImg2 - inImg))
    #imgShow(inImg2)
    #imgShow(inImg - inImg2)
    #np.savetxt("big.txt", inData2)
    #np.savetxt("small.txt", refData2)

    identity = np.diag([1,1,1,1])
    inp = nb.Nifti1Image(inData, affine=identity)
    nb.save(inp, "benchmark2/goodsims/sim" + str(iters) + "inp.nii.gz")
    ref = nb.Nifti1Image(refData, affine=identity)
    nb.save(ref, "benchmark2/goodsims/sim" + str(iters) + "ref.nii.gz")
    
    (field, invField) = imgMetamorphosis(inImg, refImg, iterations=100, verbose=True)
    defInImg = imgApplyField(inImg, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
    
    temp = nb.Nifti1Image(itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg), affine=identity)
    nb.save(temp, "benchmark2/metamorphedgoodsims/sim" + str(iters) + ".nii.gz")
    
    imgShow(inImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(refImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(defInImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(refImg - defInImg, numSlices=1)
    
    preError = imgMSE(inImg, refImg)
    postError = imgMSE(defInImg, refImg)
    print(preError)
    print(postError)
    print("")
    print("")
    preGoodSimNdregErrors.append(preError)
    postGoodSimNdregErrors.append(postError)

%matplotlib inline

from ndreg import *
import math
import numpy as np
import SimpleITK as itk
import nibabel as nb

preBadSimNdregErrors = []
postBadSimNdregErrors = []

for iters in range(10):
    print("sim " + str(iters))
    
    n = 100
    a = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    b = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    c = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    d = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    e = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    f = np.random.randint(low=n*0.25, high=n*0.75, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    r = np.random.randint(low=n*0.1, high=n*0.25, size=1, dtype=np.int16)[0]
    y,x = np.ogrid[-a:n-a, -b:n-b]
    v,w = np.ogrid[-d:n-d, -e:n-e]
    mask = x*x + y*y <= r*r
    mask2 = w*w + v*v <= r*r
    mask3 = w*w + v*v <= (r-(n/20))*(r-(n/20))

    checkers = 255*np.ones((n,n))
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(n):
            if (i % (n/5) == 0) and (j % (n/5) == 0):
                checkers[i:i+(n/10), j:j+(n/10)] = 128
            if (i % (n/5) == (n/10)) and (j % (n/5) == (n/10)):
                checkers[i:i+(n/10), j:j+(n/10)] = 128
        
    inData = np.zeros((n,n))
    inData[(d-r):(d+r),(e-r):(e+r)] = checkers[(d-r):(d+r),(e-r):(e+r)]
    #inData = inData.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    inImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(inData)
    refData = np.zeros((n,n))
    refData[mask2] = checkers[mask2]
    refData[mask] = checkers[mask]
    refData[mask3] = 0
    #refData = refData.astype(np.float32, copy=False)
    refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(refData)

    identity = np.diag([1,1,1,1])
    inp = nb.Nifti1Image(inData, affine=identity)
    nb.save(inp, "benchmark2/badsims/sim" + str(iters) + "inp.nii.gz")
    ref = nb.Nifti1Image(refData, affine=identity)
    nb.save(ref, "benchmark2/badsims/sim" + str(iters) + "ref.nii.gz")
    
    (field, invField) = imgMetamorphosis(inImg, refImg, iterations=100, verbose=True)
    defInImg = imgApplyField(inImg, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
    
    temp = nb.Nifti1Image(itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg), affine=identity)
    nb.save(temp, "benchmark2/metamorphedbadsims/sim" + str(iters) + ".nii.gz")
    
    imgShow(inImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(refImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(defInImg, numSlices=1)
    imgShow(refImg - defInImg, numSlices=1)
    
    preError = imgMSE(inImg, refImg)
    postError = imgMSE(defInImg, refImg)
    print(preError)
    print(postError)
    print("")
    print("")
    preBadSimNdregErrors.append(preError)
    postBadSimNdregErrors.append(postError)

import nibabel as nb

preBadBNU1NdregErrors = []
postBadBNU1NdregErrors = []

reference = nb.load("/home/tanay/MNI152_T1_2mm_brain.nii.gz").get_data()
refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(reference)
maskData = nb.load("/home/tanay/MNI152_T1_2mm_brain_mask.nii.gz").get_data()
maskImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(maskData)

for subject in range(864,865):
    for session in range(1,2):
        print(str(subject) + " " + str(session))
        filename = "BNU_1_0025" + str(subject) + "_" + str(session) + "_rest.nii.gz"
        brain = nb.load("/home/tanay/resampledBNU1/" + filename).get_data()
        brainslice = brain[:,:,:,0]
        inImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(brainslice)
        reference = nb.load("/home/tanay/MNI152_T1_2mm_brain.nii.gz").get_data()
        refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(reference)
        
        (field, invField) = imgMetamorphosisComposite(inImg, refImg, inMask=maskImg, alphaList=[0.05, 0.02, 0.01], iterations=100, verbose=True)
        defInImg = imgApplyField(inImg, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
        
        newbrain = np.zeros(brain.shape)
        newbrain[:,:,:,0] = itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg)
        
        for step in range(1, brain.shape[3]):
            brainslice = brain[:,:,:,step]
            imgslice = itk.GetImageFromArray(brainslice)
            regslice = imgApplyField(imgslice, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
            newbrain[:,:,:,step] = itk.GetArrayFromImage(regslice)
            
        identity = np.diag([1,1,1,1])
        newbrainimg = nb.Nifti1Image(newbrain, affine=identity)
        nb.save(newbrainimg, "/home/tanay/ndreg/benchmark2/metamorphedBNU1bad/" + filename)
            
        imgShow(inImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(refImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(defInImg, numSlices=1)
        plt.imshow(itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg))
        imgShow(refImg - defInImg, numSlices=1)
        
        preError = imgMSE(inImg, refImg)
        postError = imgMSE(defInImg, refImg)
        print(preError)
        print(postError)
        preBadBNU1NdregErrors.append(preError)
        postBadBNU1NdregErrors.append(postError)

import nibabel as nb

preGoodBNU1NdregErrors = []
postGoodBNU1NdregErrors = []

reference = nb.load("/home/tanay/MNI152_T1_2mm_brain.nii.gz").get_data()
refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(reference)

for subject in range(864,865):
    for session in range(1,2):
        print(str(subject) + " " + str(session))
        filename = "BNU_1_0025" + str(subject) + "_" + str(session) + "_rest.nii.gz"
        brain = nb.load("/home/tanay/ndreg/affinedBNU1/" + filename).get_data()
        brainslice = brain[:,:,:,0]
        inImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(brainslice)
        
        inImg.SetSpacing([1,1,1]) # Set Image spacing in mm
        inImg_ds = imgResample(inImg, [2,2,2]) # Downsample image
        refImg.SetSpacing([1,1,1]) # Set Image spacing in mm
        refImg_ds = imgResample(refImg, [2,2,2]) # Downsample image
        
        (field, invField) = imgMetamorphosisComposite(inImg_ds, refImg_ds, iterations=100, verbose=True, useMI=True)
        defInImg = imgApplyField(inImg, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
            
        imgShow(inImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(refImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(defInImg, numSlices=1)
        plt.imshow(itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg)[:,:,itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg).shape[2]/2])
        
        preError = imgMSE(inImg, refImg)
        postError = imgMSE(defInImg, refImg)
        print(preError)
        print(postError)
        preGoodBNU1NdregErrors.append(preError)
        postGoodBNU1NdregErrors.append(postError)

import nibabel as nb

preGoodBNU1NdregErrors = []
postGoodBNU1NdregErrors = []

reference = nb.load("/home/tanay/MNI152_T1_2mm_brain.nii.gz").get_data()
refImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(reference)

for subject in range(864,910):
    for session in range(1,3):
        print(str(subject) + " " + str(session))
        filename = "BNU_1_0025" + str(subject) + "_" + str(session) + "_rest.nii.gz"
        brain = nb.load("/home/tanay/ndreg/affinedBNU1/" + filename).get_data()
        brainslice = brain[:,:,:,0]
        inImg = itk.GetImageFromArray(brainslice)
        
        inImg.SetSpacing([1,1,1]) # Set Image spacing in mm
        inImg_ds = imgResample(inImg, [2,2,2]) # Downsample image
        refImg.SetSpacing([1,1,1]) # Set Image spacing in mm
        refImg_ds = imgResample(refImg, [2,2,2]) # Downsample image
        
        (field, invField) = imgMetamorphosisComposite(inImg, refImg, iterations=100, verbose=True, useMI=True)
        defInImg = imgApplyField(inImg, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
        
        newbrain = np.zeros(brain.shape)
        newbrain[:,:,:,0] = itk.GetArrayFromImage(defInImg)
        
        for step in range(1, brain.shape[3]):
            brainslice = brain[:,:,:,step]
            imgslice = itk.GetImageFromArray(brainslice)
            regslice = imgApplyField(imgslice, field, size=refImg.GetSize())
            newbrain[:,:,:,step] = itk.GetArrayFromImage(regslice)
            
        #identity = np.diag([1,1,1,1])
        #newbrainimg = nb.Nifti1Image(newbrain, affine=identity)
        #nb.save(newbrainimg, "/home/tanay/ndreg/benchmark2/metamorphedBNU1good/" + filename)
            
        imgShow(inImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(refImg, numSlices=1)
        imgShow(defInImg, numSlices=1)
        
        preError = imgMSE(inImg, refImg)
        postError = imgMSE(defInImg, refImg)
        print(preError)
        print(postError)
        preGoodBNU1NdregErrors.append(preError)
        postGoodBNU1NdregErrors.append(postError)
